    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "To clarify the screen/tmux point: I run into this issue when IPython is run outside tmux, because the Ctrl-\\ binding is in my muscle memory. As a result, sometimes I hit the keycombo forgetting that I'm outside tmux, and poof, there goes the IPython session.\r\n\r\nAt the very least, it would be very useful to have an option to disable this binding.  This has come up as an issue in the past for readline (see https://stackoverflow.com/questions/21255480/preventing-sigquit-from-terminating-interactive-python/21255589), but the proposed solutions no longer work."
